"'We are for the waiver at the WTO, we are for what the proponents of the waiver are trying to accomplish, which is better access, more manufacturing capability, more shots in arms,' US trade representative Katherine Tai said in an interview on Wednesday [5 May 2021]."

"The US isn't the only country that until now has withheld support for the waiver. The European Union, UK, Japan, Switzerland, Brazil and Norway also have resisted the push. However, supporters of the waiver argue that US leadership on the issue could help sway other holdouts." - Mod.LK]

