[Data by country, area, or territory for 6 May 2021 can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/2021%20WHO%20Daily%20Tables%20May6_1620417208.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 23.2% of daily case numbers and 39.1% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours and maintained its position as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 62.91 million cases. Brazil reported over 77 000 cases over the last 24 hours, followed by the USA with 44 834 cases, Argentina (26 238), and Colombia (14 551); 12 additional countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours (Canada, Mexico, Peru, Chile, Paraguay, Bolivia, Ecuador, Costa Rica, Honduras, Cuba, Guatemala, and Uruguay). Venezuela reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The European region reported 17.9% of daily case numbers and 22.5% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, and total cumulative cases reported exceed 52.44 million cases. Many countries not reporting cases in the last 24 hours or longer include Belgium (2 case), Switzerland (3 cases), and Kazakhstan, among others. Turkey reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours, followed by France and Germany, reporting more than 10 000 new cases in the past 24 hours. Another 19 countries reported more than 1000 cases, and an additional 3 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 4.7% of daily case numbers and 5.8% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 9.31 million cases. Iran reported the highest number of cases (15 872) over the last 24 hours, followed by Iraq, Pakistan, UAE, Kuwait, Tunisia, Jordan, Saudi Arabia, Lebanon, Bahrain, and Egypt. Qatar, Oman, and Palestinian Authority reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The African region reported 1.1% of daily case numbers and 1.4% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 3.34 million cases. Cameroon (4126) reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours, followed by South Africa (2073). Ethiopia (785) reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases. Botswana, Mauritius, and Congo, among others, did not report any new cases in the past 24 hours.

- The Western Pacific region reported 1.3% of daily case numbers and 1.3% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 2.53 million cases. Philippines reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours (over 5000 cases), followed by Japan, Malaysia, Mongolia, and South Korea.

- The South East Asia region reported 51.0% of the daily newly reported cases and 29.2% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 24.26 million cases. India is dominant, reporting over 412 000 cases, followed by Nepal (8605), Indonesia (5285), Sri Lanka (1939), Thailand (1911), and Bangladesh (1742).

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 6 May 2021, is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod.UBA]

